<HEAD>GCC Ministers Meet</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: grafs 1-3 new to UPDATE with opening comments, uppicks 2nd
graf pvs: Four of ...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>RIYADH, Saudi Arabia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Saudi Arabian Oil Minister <PERSON> Hisham </PERSON> <PERSON> Nazer </PERSON> called for `` solidarity to bring us all good'' as he opened a meeting Sunday with five other members of the <ORGANIZATION> Gulf </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cooperation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION>. The minister's statement, carried by the official Saudi press agency, said that low oil prices brought on by overproduction require joint action `` to bring prosperity to our nation and countries.'' The report did not outline what plan <PERSON> Nazer </PERSON> might present during the meeting, called to forge a joint strategy to help <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> prop up deteriorating oil prices. Four of the six <ORGANIZATION> GCC </ORGANIZATION> members _ <LOCATION> Saudi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Arabia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Qatar </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Arab </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Emirates </LOCATION> _ are ranking members of the 13-nation Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries. While <ORGANIZATION> GCC </ORGANIZATION> members <LOCATION> Oman </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Bahrain </LOCATION> are not part of <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION>, their economies depend on oil export revenues. The meeting at <ORGANIZATION> GCC </ORGANIZATION> headquarters here began early Sunday evening. The ministers did not speak to reporters before the single session began. A worldwide oil glut has sent crude prices tumbling as much as $ 8 below the $ 18-a-barrel <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> benchmark. Much of the excess crude comes from <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> producers, including <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> members collectively are pumping more than 3 million barrels in excess of the aggregate ceiling the cartel agreed to in late 1986 to try to defend the $ 18 price. Many producers have openly ignored their quotas. The <LOC